An obscure body in the SK system.
The inhabitants call it Earth.

4
00:00:35,927 --> 00:00:38,964
How peaceful it looks.

5
00:00:44,727 --> 00:00:47,082
EARTHQUAKE

6
00:00:49,687 --> 00:00:55,683
Most effective, Your Majesty.
Will you destroy this Earth?

7
00:00:55,847 --> 00:01:01,797
Later. l like to play with things ...
before annihilation.

8
00:01:16,087 --> 00:01:17,759
MAlN TlTLE

9
00:03:27,287 --> 00:03:29,403
HOT HAlL

10
00:05:16,927 --> 00:05:20,602
Green Mountain Airways 123
requesting instructions.

11
00:05:20,767 --> 00:05:25,841
l hope Flash Gordon's had
a great vacation after last season.

12
00:05:37,407 --> 00:05:41,195
- Any problem, fellas?
- Just turbulence. Nothing serious.

13
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:45,201
Nothing you'd want to toss
a third-down pass through either.

14
00:05:45,367 --> 00:05:49,645
Would you like to autograph this
for my kid, Mr. Gordon?

15
00:05:52,807 --> 00:05:56,925
- Call Boston approach.
- lt may be smoother higher up.

16
00:05:57,087 --> 00:06:01,080
Do us a favor and leave them alone.
They're busy driving the bus.

17
00:06:01,887 --> 00:06:05,675
lt's just a little turbulence.

18
00:06:05,847 --> 00:06:09,681
- My name's Flash.
- l know.

19
00:06:09,847 --> 00:06:13,760
l'm sorry if l seemed rude.
l'm just a little scared.

20
00:06:13,927 --> 00:06:18,205
lt's kind of nice.
A travel agent who's scared in planes.

21
00:06:18,367 --> 00:06:21,564
l asked the Matire D' who you were.

22
00:06:24,527 --> 00:06:29,442
- Talk to me. Get my mind off this.
- l couldn't believe you were alone.

23
00:06:29,607 --> 00:06:32,485
- You're just saying that.
- No, l mean it.

24
00:06:32,647 --> 00:06:37,801
- What were you doing there, alone?
- Trying to get my head together.

25
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:42,563
- By myself, you know?
- l sure do.

26
00:06:43,287 --> 00:06:46,165
lt's okay.
Honestly, it's nothing.

27
00:06:46,327 --> 00:06:49,205
- Famous last words.
- l take flying lessons.

28
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:53,599
Sometimes air rises above clouds
and you get a ...

29
00:06:54,727 --> 00:06:57,525
What's the matter?

30
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:05,165
What's happening, Flash?

31
00:07:38,927 --> 00:07:43,876
Dr. Zarkov! There's no sun.
lt's 8:24 in the morning.

32
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:47,244
- No sun?
- No.

33
00:07:47,407 --> 00:07:50,240
Check the angular vector
of the moon.

34
00:07:51,127 --> 00:07:56,042
<i>There seems to be no reason</i>
<i>for these intergalactic upsets.</i>

35
00:07:56,207 --> 00:08:01,440
<i>only Dr. Hans Zarkov, formerly</i>
<i>of NASA, provided an explanation.</i>

36
00:08:01,607 --> 00:08:06,397
<i>His ideas, however,</i>
<i>have been rejected as irrational.</i>

37
00:08:06,567 --> 00:08:12,437
<i>According to NASA, today's</i>
<i>solar eclipse is no cause for alarm.</i>

38
00:08:12,607 --> 00:08:17,681
<i>A team of scientists has been</i>
<i>in conference with the President.</i>

39
00:08:19,527 --> 00:08:22,599
What do you find?
The moon out of orbit?

40
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:26,885
By more than <i>tw</i>elve degrees.
lt must be a mistake.

41
00:08:27,047 --> 00:08:31,325
That's no mistake.
lt's an attack.

42
00:08:33,327 --> 00:08:37,366
l've been right all these years.

43
00:08:46,527 --> 00:08:52,762
Fragments of moon rock. Our moon
is subjected to some enormous force.

44
00:08:52,927 --> 00:08:59,036
A kind of energy beam.

45
00:08:59,207 --> 00:09:03,246
Time to go, Munson.
l've got the coordinates, -

46
00:09:03,407 --> 00:09:06,205
- the direction it's coming from.

47
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:09,359
This is what we've been waiting for.

48
00:09:09,527 --> 00:09:13,998
We'll go up and counter-attack.

49
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:18,399
You're crazy.
l'm not going up in that.

50
00:09:18,567 --> 00:09:22,845
- l can't handle the capsule alone.
- You'd better try.

51
00:09:23,007 --> 00:09:27,922
- Get your toothbrush and whatever.
- Right, chief.

52
00:09:28,087 --> 00:09:32,763
Munson!
Why are you running away?

53
00:09:34,327 --> 00:09:37,046
All the frequencies are dead.

54
00:09:37,207 --> 00:09:41,280
- Get a look at the V.O.R.
- Holy cow!

55
00:09:42,927 --> 00:09:45,999
John, ten o'clock!

56
00:09:50,207 --> 00:09:53,677
l'll put this baby down right here.

57
00:10:01,447 --> 00:10:04,245
What the hell?

58
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:12,203
- My God, where are the pilots?
- Help me pull her up.

59
00:10:21,007 --> 00:10:23,726
Are we coming up?
l can't see.

60
00:10:23,887 --> 00:10:26,720
Me neither. Look for landing lights.

61
00:10:26,887 --> 00:10:32,041
- This isn't my scene. Look where?
- Hit the switches over there.

62
00:10:32,207 --> 00:10:36,644
Did your flying lessons
get as far as landing?

63
00:10:36,807 --> 00:10:40,402
l was afraid you'd ask that. No.

64
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:43,684
Hang on, here we go.

65
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:56,876
Munson!

66
00:10:57,047 --> 00:11:00,642
l swear, Munson, l'll shoot!

67
00:11:00,807 --> 00:11:03,799
Get shot, go up,
what's the difference?

68
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:07,198
You'll give your life to save Earth.

69
00:11:07,367 --> 00:11:11,440
- Haven't you any spirit at all?
- No!

70
00:11:18,727 --> 00:11:22,322
- Dr. Zarkov, listen!
- You're back.

71
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:37,646
- Dale, you all right?
- l'm terrific.

72
00:11:37,807 --> 00:11:42,039
Let's get out of here
before she blows.

73
00:11:54,647 --> 00:11:58,481
Hold me for a second, then drop me,
l'll kiss the ground.

74
00:11:58,647 --> 00:12:02,686
- You sure you're okay?
- Fine. But no more flying.

75
00:12:05,047 --> 00:12:10,565
- Good morning! Are you injured?
- lt seems not.

76
00:12:10,727 --> 00:12:14,845
A miracle.
l expect you'd like to use my phone?

77
00:12:15,007 --> 00:12:20,286
- l would.
- l'm sure the insurance ...

78
00:12:20,447 --> 00:12:24,599
- Please, don't mention it.
- What happened to the sun?

79
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:29,921
- Looks like an eclipse.
- There was nothing about it on TV.

80
00:12:30,087 --> 00:12:33,318
The phone is right in there.

81
00:12:40,087 --> 00:12:43,841
Sorry, Munson.
Missed your opportunity.

82
00:12:44,007 --> 00:12:49,001
- Where's the telephone?
- l'm sure that's Dr. Zarkov.

83
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:51,727
He's a crazy scientist l saw on TV.

84
00:12:51,887 --> 00:12:56,483
He kept talking about an attack.
They kicked him out of NASA ...

85
00:12:56,647 --> 00:12:59,161
- Dr. Zarkov.
- Enough!

86
00:12:59,327 --> 00:13:02,160
- Are you crazy?
- Unfortunately not.

87
00:13:02,327 --> 00:13:08,516
The attack has begun. We have eleven
days before the moon crashes down.

88
00:13:08,687 --> 00:13:13,203
- l need aid in taking off.
- Taking off where?

89
00:13:13,367 --> 00:13:18,646
Up there. l need one person
to keep a foot on that red pedal -

90
00:13:18,807 --> 00:13:23,437
- during blast-off.
You're the lighter. Sit down.

91
00:13:24,687 --> 00:13:29,715
You may leave. Tell the world
what Hans Zarkov has done.

92
00:13:30,647 --> 00:13:34,845
l guess l'll be running along now.
You lunatic!

93
00:13:40,247 --> 00:13:42,477
Flash, the doors!

94
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:12,637
Sit down! Keep a foot on the pedal,
or the G-forces will kill us all.

95
00:14:12,807 --> 00:14:14,718
My God, we're moving.

96
00:14:16,287 --> 00:14:21,407
For God's sake,
strap yourselves down! Quick!

97
00:14:41,127 --> 00:14:44,085
The red pedal!

98
00:14:46,767 --> 00:14:52,080
Friendship.
Built this to send in friendship ...

99
00:14:54,087 --> 00:14:56,999
The end, now ...

100
00:14:57,167 --> 00:15:03,402
Unless we three can ...
Unless we can ...

101
00:16:11,047 --> 00:16:15,438
Strange object
in the imperial vortex.

102
00:16:15,607 --> 00:16:19,566
What distance?

103
00:16:19,727 --> 00:16:23,845
Parallel to star field Zygma 12,
approaching.

104
00:16:30,527 --> 00:16:34,964
<i>- Test object for life waves.</i>
<i>- Positive, form unknown.</i>

105
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:37,402
<i>Approximate Mong Scale 3.</i>

106
00:16:42,847 --> 00:16:47,284
<i>object entering our control range,</i>
<i>approaching the Sea of Fire.</i>

107
00:16:47,447 --> 00:16:50,996
<i>Bring it through safely. Land it.</i>

108
00:17:31,447 --> 00:17:34,996
Wake up, Dale. We're okay.

109
00:17:35,167 --> 00:17:39,285
lt's me, Flash. Remember?
We're on the ground.

110
00:17:39,887 --> 00:17:43,562
- Back home?
- l don't think so.

111
00:17:56,007 --> 00:18:00,717
Hello. We're from Earth. Friends.

112
00:18:13,367 --> 00:18:17,599
Whoever they are,
it's clear they are highly developed.

113
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:21,999
- l'm sure we can reason with them.
- Want to bet on it?

114
00:18:29,087 --> 00:18:33,080
- My God!
- ls this a Civic Reception?

115
00:18:33,247 --> 00:18:37,320
- More like a police state.
- That could be our good luck.

116
00:18:37,487 --> 00:18:40,206
lt means we'll find allies everywhere.

117
00:18:40,367 --> 00:18:44,565
They're just waiting for someone
to lead them in revolt.

118
00:18:44,727 --> 00:18:50,120
- Are you looking at me, Zarkov?
- Please. l just want to get home.

119
00:18:53,127 --> 00:18:57,439
<i>Guards, halt.</i>
<i>Prisoners, follow me.</i>

120
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:14,477
<i>Halt, Lizard Man!</i>
<i>Escape is impossible. Surrender.</i>

121
00:19:18,607 --> 00:19:22,486
<i>Prisoners, march below me</i>
<i>to Emperor Ming.</i>

122
00:19:22,647 --> 00:19:26,925
Let's not argue. Here, hold my hand.

123
00:19:27,087 --> 00:19:32,366
- You want to reason with that?
- lf it fails, l still have the gun.

124
00:19:32,527 --> 00:19:36,839
Don't worry. l'll make it plain
l'm acting on my own.

125
00:19:37,007 --> 00:19:40,716
- lt's plain suicide.
- lt's a rational transaction.

126
00:19:40,887 --> 00:19:43,799
- One life for billions.
- <i>Halt!</i>

127
00:19:52,087 --> 00:19:54,521
<i>Proceed.</i>

128
00:20:47,607 --> 00:20:52,681
Hail Ming, hail!
Ruler of the universe!

129
00:20:52,847 --> 00:20:57,716
Hail, Ming! Emperor of the galaxy!

130
00:20:57,887 --> 00:21:01,721
The tributes of the Hawkmen
will be first.

131
00:21:04,007 --> 00:21:07,079
- Are we dreaming?
- l'd like to think so.

132
00:21:07,247 --> 00:21:12,640
The fabled lce Jewel of Frigia.

133
00:21:12,807 --> 00:21:16,436
- We seized it in battle.
- Stop!

134
00:21:18,927 --> 00:21:23,523
The lce Jewel is our tribute,
not Vultan's.

135
00:21:24,327 --> 00:21:28,479
Vultan stole it
while we were burying our dead.

136
00:21:28,647 --> 00:21:31,957
- You are a thief.
- What?

137
00:21:34,927 --> 00:21:37,725
Let down your weapons!

138
00:21:39,487 --> 00:21:43,605
No one, but no one,
dies in the palace -

139
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:47,362
- without a command
from the Emperor.

140
00:21:53,247 --> 00:21:55,886
Hail Ming.

141
00:21:58,767 --> 00:22:04,364
You obey ...
Or you sacrifice your daughter.

142
00:22:12,367 --> 00:22:14,756
Hail Ming.

143
00:22:18,247 --> 00:22:22,286
Now the tributes from Ardentia.

144
00:22:23,647 --> 00:22:27,845
Your Majesty,
we, the people of Ardentia, -

145
00:22:28,007 --> 00:22:31,283
- have suffered
since you blasted our kingdom.

146
00:22:31,447 --> 00:22:35,281
l can offer you nothing
except my loyalty.

147
00:22:35,447 --> 00:22:40,237
Prince Thun,
we prize nothing more highly.

148
00:22:40,407 --> 00:22:45,037
- And how great is this loyalty?
- Without measure.

149
00:22:45,207 --> 00:22:49,758
We are delighted to hear it.
Fall on your sword.

150
00:22:51,647 --> 00:22:56,562
Show us this loyalty.
Throw yourself onto your sword.

151
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:18,800
May this deed of Prince Thun be an
example to all the kingdoms of Mongo.

152
00:23:18,967 --> 00:23:21,925
Death to Ming!

153
00:23:55,527 --> 00:23:59,645
- This Ming's a psycho.
- <i>This Ming is a psycho.</i>

154
00:23:59,807 --> 00:24:04,961
- Who said that?
<i>- The fair-haired prisoner.</i>

155
00:24:28,687 --> 00:24:30,837
Come along, Fellini.

156
00:24:36,527 --> 00:24:38,518
Remember me?

157
00:24:46,567 --> 00:24:52,085
- Who are you?
- Flash Gordon. Quarterback.

158
00:24:52,247 --> 00:24:57,480
Dale Arden, Your Highness.
Live and let live, that's my motto.

159
00:24:57,647 --> 00:25:03,643
l'm Hans Zarkov. l kidnapped them
in an effort to save our planet Earth.

160
00:25:03,807 --> 00:25:09,757
An obscure body, which has given you
so much amusement recently.

161
00:25:09,927 --> 00:25:15,047
We're only interested in friendship.
Why do you attack us?

162
00:25:15,207 --> 00:25:18,085
Why not?

163
00:25:18,247 --> 00:25:24,561
Pathetic earthlings.
Hurling your bodies into the void, -

164
00:25:24,727 --> 00:25:28,481
- without an inkling of
who or what is out here.

165
00:25:28,647 --> 00:25:34,005
lf you knew anything about
the Universe, you'd hide from it.

166
00:25:35,967 --> 00:25:39,004
Come closer.
Not you!

167
00:25:39,167 --> 00:25:43,604
- You. Let us see you.
- No.

168
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:56,486
- Dale!
- Don't.

169
00:26:28,367 --> 00:26:33,236
- Did you ever see such response?
- No. Truly.

170
00:26:33,407 --> 00:26:36,479
She even rivals your daughter.

171
00:26:47,487 --> 00:26:51,241
- What happened?
- Don't know, but it was sensational.

172
00:26:51,407 --> 00:26:54,683
Remove the Earth woman.

173
00:26:54,847 --> 00:26:58,886
Prepare her for our pleasure.

174
00:27:01,487 --> 00:27:05,799
Forget it, Ming. Dale's with me.

175
00:27:07,807 --> 00:27:11,800
- Stay back!
- Don't, Flash, they'll kill you.

176
00:27:26,967 --> 00:27:30,926
l'll go with them, just ...
You ..!

177
00:27:58,727 --> 00:28:00,683
Klytus!

178
00:28:01,687 --> 00:28:04,918
Are your men on the right pills?

179
00:28:06,367 --> 00:28:09,962
Maybe you should execute
their trainer.

180
00:28:21,287 --> 00:28:23,562
Come here!

181
00:28:23,727 --> 00:28:28,881
You fools. He's playing some
barbaric game. Match him, like this.

182
00:28:33,247 --> 00:28:37,604
- Forty one! Forty <i>tw</i>o!
- Go, Flash, go.

183
00:28:40,327 --> 00:28:43,399
Go, Flash, go!

184
00:29:15,127 --> 00:29:17,960
Don't kill him yet, Father.

185
00:29:18,127 --> 00:29:22,757
l want him.
Give him to me.

186
00:29:23,407 --> 00:29:26,558
What would Prince Barin say?

187
00:29:26,727 --> 00:29:31,084
l can handle Barin.
Please ...

188
00:29:33,567 --> 00:29:37,162
Really, Aura. Your appetites
are too dangerous. l refuse.

189
00:29:37,327 --> 00:29:43,243
Guards! Deliver the scientist
to General Klytus for conditioning.

190
00:29:43,407 --> 00:29:47,082
This one has defied us
before our subjects.

191
00:29:47,247 --> 00:29:52,037
We order him disposed of tonight
by public execution.

192
00:29:54,487 --> 00:30:00,084
<i>This is a public announcement.</i>
<i>Flash Gordon is to be executed-</i>

193
00:30:00,247 --> 00:30:04,320
<i>- at 29.15 Mingo mean time.</i>

194
00:30:04,487 --> 00:30:09,641
Fly back to your kingdom.
You may see me sooner than you think.

195
00:30:14,087 --> 00:30:18,239
- Lying bitch.
- l'll come.

196
00:30:18,407 --> 00:30:24,084
lf you rocket there right away.
l've a surprise for you.

197
00:30:24,247 --> 00:30:28,718
- Don't you love me?
- l don't trust you.

198
00:30:31,287 --> 00:30:34,438
Just be there.

199
00:30:44,287 --> 00:30:47,404
l demand to see the Governor.

200
00:30:51,087 --> 00:30:54,477
l can hardly breathe in this thing.

201
00:30:55,447 --> 00:31:00,726
Yes, you don't look well. And l'm told
you refused your final meal.

202
00:31:00,887 --> 00:31:05,085
- The chef will be upset.
- Tell him to go to hell!

203
00:31:05,247 --> 00:31:10,844
Gas works more quickly
on an empty stomach. Any requests?

204
00:31:11,007 --> 00:31:16,479
- Let me see Dale right away.
- Oh, dear. How pathetic.

205
00:31:16,647 --> 00:31:19,764
Yes, l anticipated that.

206
00:31:19,927 --> 00:31:23,966
Bring in the Emperor's concubine.

207
00:31:24,127 --> 00:31:29,440
- Oh, my God!
- l said l want to see her!

208
00:31:32,967 --> 00:31:37,757
You have until the sands run out.

209
00:31:42,927 --> 00:31:45,521
Pathetic ...

210
00:31:48,767 --> 00:31:54,364
You look great.
No kidding, you look great.

211
00:31:54,527 --> 00:31:59,726
lt's the eye make-up. l hope
l remember the trick when l wake up.

212
00:31:59,887 --> 00:32:03,402
That's exactly
what l was gonna tell you.

213
00:32:03,567 --> 00:32:08,004
This isn't happening.
lt's just a bad dream.

214
00:32:08,167 --> 00:32:10,158
l agree completely.

215
00:32:10,327 --> 00:32:15,355
We'll wake up any minute
in Dark Harbor and laugh about this.

216
00:32:16,327 --> 00:32:21,117
Only, next time l'll walk over
and talk to you.

217
00:32:21,287 --> 00:32:25,838
- Promise?
- Cross my heart and hope to ...

218
00:32:26,767 --> 00:32:31,522
- l really will talk to you, Dale.
- What if we're wrong?

219
00:32:31,687 --> 00:32:36,920
- What if it isn't a dream?
- You'll find Zarkov, save the Earth.

220
00:32:37,087 --> 00:32:41,558
He'll get you home in the capsule.
Don't think of me, think of ...

221
00:32:43,527 --> 00:32:46,121
Don't look at it.

222
00:32:48,847 --> 00:32:53,079
lt won't turn over ...
lt won't turn over.

223
00:33:44,127 --> 00:33:49,042
Did you enjoy yourselves on Sybaria?
l hear you flew the Doctor there.

224
00:33:49,207 --> 00:33:53,325
Klytus kindly fed me the information.

225
00:33:53,487 --> 00:33:57,366
He wants me himself. His agents
are always making up lies about me.

226
00:34:34,447 --> 00:34:39,840
Look!
Water is leaking from her eyes.

227
00:34:40,007 --> 00:34:44,683
lt's what they call tears,
a sign of their weakness.

228
00:35:01,087 --> 00:35:03,965
This will help you on your way.

229
00:35:27,887 --> 00:35:30,401
Flash!

230
00:35:55,647 --> 00:35:59,276
