EARTHLlNG EXECUTED BY MlNG

231
00:36:14,407 --> 00:36:16,477
Hurry.

232
00:36:23,127 --> 00:36:27,803
You know what happens
if l'm found out.

233
00:36:27,967 --> 00:36:31,403
l'm a fool for you, Aura.

234
00:36:32,687 --> 00:36:36,646
There we are. Sybaria again,
same place, next weekend?

235
00:36:36,807 --> 00:36:39,605
l can hardly wait.

236
00:37:04,167 --> 00:37:10,356
- Where am l?
- Back from the dead. l saved you.

237
00:37:10,527 --> 00:37:14,486
- How?
- By magic, of course.

238
00:37:14,647 --> 00:37:19,801
- With a kiss, because l like you.
- Where's Dale and Zarkov?

239
00:37:19,967 --> 00:37:25,439
They're safe. Put this uniform on
before the Lizard Men come.

240
00:37:27,607 --> 00:37:30,804
Don't worry, l won't look.

241
00:37:32,527 --> 00:37:34,802
l like you a lot.

242
00:37:40,727 --> 00:37:44,515
- Where are you taking me?
- To the moon Arboria.

243
00:37:44,687 --> 00:37:47,759
l've got to rescue my friends
and save Earth.

244
00:37:47,927 --> 00:37:52,205
Pretty risky telling that
to the Emperor's daughter.

245
00:37:54,967 --> 00:37:59,006
- What's in Arboria?
- People who'll help you.

246
00:37:59,167 --> 00:38:02,955
- Prince Barin does anything l ask.
- That's Zarkov!

247
00:38:06,327 --> 00:38:10,445
They're just conditioning him
to our climate. Keep out of sight.

248
00:38:14,527 --> 00:38:20,523
Every thousand years l test
each life system in the universe.

249
00:38:20,687 --> 00:38:26,717
l visit it with mysteries,
earthquakes, unpredicted eclipses.

250
00:38:27,487 --> 00:38:30,604
Strange craters in the wilderness.

251
00:38:30,767 --> 00:38:35,443
lf these are taken as natural, l judge
that system ignorant and harmless.

252
00:38:35,607 --> 00:38:42,080
l spare it. But if the hand of Ming
is recognized in these events, -

253
00:38:42,247 --> 00:38:49,483
- l judge that system dangerous.
l call upon the great god Dyzan.

254
00:38:49,647 --> 00:38:55,722
And for his greater glory,
and our mutual pleasure ...

255
00:38:58,047 --> 00:39:01,323
l destroy it utterly.

256
00:39:01,487 --> 00:39:06,561
So it's my fault
Earth is being destroyed?

257
00:39:06,727 --> 00:39:09,719
Precisely, Doctor.

258
00:39:11,607 --> 00:39:17,079
l thought it might amuse you to
know this, before your mind is gone.

259
00:39:19,687 --> 00:39:22,155
Proceed with it.

260
00:39:27,527 --> 00:39:31,042
What are you doing to me?

261
00:39:31,207 --> 00:39:34,677
We're just emptying your mind.

262
00:39:34,847 --> 00:39:40,205
We are going to empty your memory
as we might empty your pockets ...

263
00:39:41,087 --> 00:39:46,207
- Doctor ...
- No, don't. Please. l beg you.

264
00:39:46,367 --> 00:39:51,361
My mind is all l have. l've spent
my whole life trying to fill it.

265
00:39:51,527 --> 00:39:54,200
Begin.

266
00:40:37,367 --> 00:40:39,961
Now he showed promise.

267
00:40:56,527 --> 00:40:59,166
Papa!

268
00:41:21,367 --> 00:41:24,404
- Hold it there.
- Reprogram now?

269
00:41:24,567 --> 00:41:27,206
Yes.

270
00:41:28,127 --> 00:41:33,247
But don't fill him with anything above
level three. His mind can't take it.

271
00:41:33,407 --> 00:41:36,399
l understand. Level three only.

272
00:41:36,567 --> 00:41:39,161
l have to attend to something.

273
00:41:39,327 --> 00:41:44,037
- Can you manage without me?
- l'll try.

274
00:41:44,207 --> 00:41:46,596
l'll return.

275
00:41:47,967 --> 00:41:50,322
Begin to reprogram.

276
00:41:52,527 --> 00:41:57,203
Continue to level six.
l gave you an order.

277
00:41:57,367 --> 00:42:00,564
Program the subject to level six.

278
00:42:12,567 --> 00:42:15,206
Try again.

279
00:42:15,367 --> 00:42:21,397
Your left hand controls direction,
right does the altitude.

280
00:42:22,887 --> 00:42:26,243
And use your fingers too this time.

281
00:42:30,727 --> 00:42:35,403
Gently, darling,
it's extremely sensitive ...

282
00:42:35,567 --> 00:42:39,196
- Like me.
- What's that?

283
00:42:39,367 --> 00:42:42,359
The planet Aquaria.

284
00:42:48,087 --> 00:42:53,559
Now take a left over Frigia,
the next moon rising.

285
00:42:56,767 --> 00:43:03,400
Every moon of Mongo is a kingdom.
My father keeps them fighting.

286
00:43:03,567 --> 00:43:08,766
lt's a really brilliant strategy.

287
00:43:08,927 --> 00:43:14,399
- Why don't they team up against him?
- Team up? What does that mean?

288
00:43:14,567 --> 00:43:19,004
- Maybe l'll show you sometime.
- Wonderful.

289
00:43:19,167 --> 00:43:23,718
You can do it
when l take you to Cythera.

290
00:43:23,887 --> 00:43:28,165
lt's my secret pleasure moon.
l have a little palace there, -

291
00:43:28,327 --> 00:43:31,399
-just for <i>tw</i>o.

292
00:43:31,567 --> 00:43:35,355
- Wait a minute.
- Oh, Flash, l saved your life.

293
00:43:45,767 --> 00:43:49,726
Drink this.
lt has no name.

294
00:43:49,887 --> 00:43:54,165
Many brave men died to bring it here
from the Galaxy of Pleasure.

295
00:43:54,327 --> 00:43:59,606
lt will make your nights with Ming
more agreeable.

296
00:43:59,767 --> 00:44:02,327
- Will it make me forget?
- No.

297
00:44:02,487 --> 00:44:06,116
But it will make you not mind
remembering.

298
00:44:15,087 --> 00:44:17,806
This isn't bad at all.

299
00:44:23,087 --> 00:44:28,923
lt's a thought amplifier. l'm going to
think to Barin to expect us.

300
00:44:29,087 --> 00:44:32,875
- You're kidding. Think to him?
- Of course.

301
00:44:33,047 --> 00:44:38,599
- Don't you have telepathy on Earth?
- Could l call Dale on this?

302
00:44:38,767 --> 00:44:44,080
- lf l showed you how. But l won't.
- Please, show me.

303
00:44:44,247 --> 00:44:49,002
You'll have to persuade me
much better than that.

304
00:44:52,327 --> 00:44:57,765
What are you doing? Are you mad?
Let go, we're diving into Frigia.

305
00:44:57,927 --> 00:45:02,125
- Pull up.
- Just tune me in to Dale.

306
00:45:10,167 --> 00:45:15,446
<i>Dale, it's me, Flash.</i>
<i>Are you getting me?</i>

307
00:45:17,047 --> 00:45:22,963
Oh, my head.
lf it only was you.

308
00:45:23,127 --> 00:45:28,679
- She's not getting me.
- Use your brain.

309
00:45:30,807 --> 00:45:36,120
<i>l'm with you, Dale. Just concentrate</i>
<i>hard. lt's telepathy.</i>

310
00:45:36,287 --> 00:45:40,963
<i>Can this be real?</i>
<i>l saw you executed.</i>

311
00:45:41,127 --> 00:45:46,565
<i>- l was saved.</i>
<i>- Thank God. Where are you?</i>

312
00:45:46,727 --> 00:45:51,278
<i>ln a rocket to Arboria, to get help.</i>
<i>Are you okay?</i>

313
00:45:51,447 --> 00:45:56,965
<i>- l'm locked in Ming's bedroom.</i>
<i>- Fake him out. Girls know how.</i>

314
00:45:57,127 --> 00:46:00,802
lt's been done to me.
<i>Fake him out till l get back</i>.

315
00:46:00,967 --> 00:46:05,597
<i>lt's too dangerous for you here.</i>
<i>Stay where you're safe.</i>

316
00:46:05,767 --> 00:46:10,795
<i>- This girl really turns me on ...</i>
<i>- l didn't quite get that.</i>

317
00:46:12,247 --> 00:46:17,082
<i>- lt wasn't about you.</i>
<i>- What?</i>

318
00:46:17,247 --> 00:46:21,240
<i>l've got to go, someone's coming.</i>
<i>Got to stop thinking to each other.</i>

319
00:46:24,447 --> 00:46:29,043
His lmperial Highness
will be here very soon.

320
00:46:29,207 --> 00:46:32,597
- Shall l pour?
- Please.

321
00:46:34,367 --> 00:46:40,237
- Wouldn't you like a sip?
- No, it's forbidden for us slaves.

322
00:46:40,407 --> 00:46:44,446
lt's quality stuff, have some.

323
00:46:45,687 --> 00:46:50,715
We're all girls here, l won't tell.
Just one sip.

324
00:46:50,887 --> 00:46:53,845
Live a little.

325
00:47:01,207 --> 00:47:03,562
Bottoms up.

326
00:47:07,887 --> 00:47:10,879
- What is your name?
- Hans Zarkov.

327
00:47:11,047 --> 00:47:16,644
Agent Zarkov! Number 2133 of the
Anti-lnsurgent Espionage Group.

328
00:47:16,807 --> 00:47:19,480
Hail Ming.

329
00:47:19,647 --> 00:47:21,763
Good.

330
00:47:47,247 --> 00:47:51,638
- lt's not usually so bad.
- How far to the landing pad?

331
00:47:51,807 --> 00:47:55,277
Six point four. l'll drop the flaps.

332
00:48:49,887 --> 00:48:52,196
You?

333
00:49:09,447 --> 00:49:11,881
Over here.

334
00:49:16,567 --> 00:49:18,842
Hey buddy!

335
00:50:14,847 --> 00:50:20,319
l've got her.
Sector 409 beta.

336
00:50:20,487 --> 00:50:23,445
Activate Agent Zarkov.

337
00:50:41,327 --> 00:50:45,240
<i>Dr. Zarkov.</i>
<i>You're a sight for sore eyes.</i>

338
00:50:45,407 --> 00:50:49,161
<i>- Rest a minute.</i>
<i>- l can't.</i>

339
00:50:49,327 --> 00:50:52,717
<i>We've got to join up with Flash.</i>
<i>He's alive.</i>

340
00:50:52,887 --> 00:50:57,199
<i>l talked to him by telepathy.</i>
<i>He went to Arboria to get help.</i>

341
00:50:57,367 --> 00:51:01,076
<i>- lncredible.</i>
<i>- There's soldiers everywhere.</i>

342
00:51:01,247 --> 00:51:03,966
<i>- Let me think a moment.</i>
- Unseal the city.

343
00:51:04,127 --> 00:51:10,123
- Allow her to exit with Zarkov.
- <i>l think l can find a way out.</i>

344
00:51:10,287 --> 00:51:13,085
<i>No questions, just follow me.</i>

345
00:51:17,967 --> 00:51:22,006
Dale Arden is under the guidance
of Agent Zarkov.

346
00:51:22,167 --> 00:51:27,799
- But Flash Gordon is still alive.
- He was revived by a traitor.

347
00:51:27,967 --> 00:51:32,279
And spirited from the city.
We know this from the Earth girl.

348
00:51:32,447 --> 00:51:38,079
- What traitor?
- l have my suspicions.

349
00:51:38,247 --> 00:51:42,001
- Stop at nothing.
- No matter to whom the trail leads?

350
00:51:42,167 --> 00:51:45,204
l said at nothing.

351
00:51:57,727 --> 00:52:01,003
- What's that?
- Their sacred temple.

352
00:52:01,167 --> 00:52:06,321
A young man is being initiated.
But we must hide till it's done.

353
00:52:37,607 --> 00:52:39,723
l love initiations.

354
00:52:48,007 --> 00:52:51,966
l am now of age, Green Father.
l ask for the test of manhood.

355
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:57,838
Choose your passage,
into this world, or the next.

356
00:52:58,007 --> 00:53:01,556
May Arbor guide you.

357
00:53:56,967 --> 00:54:00,403
Send me on my way.

358
00:54:00,567 --> 00:54:05,197
- Spare me the madness.
- l will. Hold him.

359
00:54:12,127 --> 00:54:16,279
- This guy is going to help me?
- Stay.

360
00:54:22,567 --> 00:54:28,039
That was extremely moving.
l do sometimes keep a promise.

361
00:54:33,967 --> 00:54:38,836
- Prepare a feast.
- No, l have to get back right away.

362
00:54:39,007 --> 00:54:45,082
- Then why did you come?
- l brought you a present. Flash?

363
00:54:52,567 --> 00:54:55,479
Welcome back from the grave.

364
00:54:55,647 --> 00:54:58,684
l knew you were up to something,
but not necrophilia.

365
00:54:58,847 --> 00:55:02,601
Just keep him for me until my father
has had his way with Dale Arden.

366
00:55:02,767 --> 00:55:07,761
l'll keep him all right! ln my larder.
Take him, with the rest of the meat.

367
00:55:07,927 --> 00:55:13,638
l forbid it. lf you kill Flash,
you'll never have me again.

368
00:55:14,647 --> 00:55:19,323
What danger is there?
Everyone thinks he's dead.

369
00:55:19,487 --> 00:55:24,356
- l'll take him to Cythera next week.
- Harboring a fugitive is treason.

370
00:55:24,527 --> 00:55:28,361
You're not frightened of Ming.

371
00:55:30,407 --> 00:55:34,525
- You are playing with fire, Aura.
- Of course l am.

372
00:55:42,487 --> 00:55:43,761
Does anyone ever trust her <i>tw</i>ice?

373
00:55:45,327 --> 00:55:48,842
So they let us escape because Klytus
thought he erased your memory.

374
00:55:49,007 --> 00:55:56,846
Do you know why it failed? l started
to recite Shakespeare, the Talmud, -

375
00:55:57,007 --> 00:56:04,243
- Einstein, anything l could remember,
even The Beatles. lt armored me.

376
00:56:04,407 --> 00:56:09,527
They couldn't wipe those things away.
You can't beat the human spirit.

377
00:56:16,327 --> 00:56:21,959
Prince Barin! l'm not your enemy,
Ming is. And you know it.

378
00:56:22,127 --> 00:56:27,326
Ming is the enemy of every creature
on Mongo. Let's team up and fight him.

379
00:56:29,647 --> 00:56:32,684
Lower them into the swamp.

380
00:56:34,527 --> 00:56:36,757
We can do it, Barin!

381
00:57:00,487 --> 00:57:05,242
Your lover Barin is harboring
Gordon, is he not?

382
00:57:05,407 --> 00:57:07,762
This lying is such a waste of time.

383
00:57:07,927 --> 00:57:13,081
You left with a pilot and returned
alone. Wasn't he Gordon?

384
00:57:14,407 --> 00:57:18,719
Who do you think you're protecting?
The lmperial Surgeon?

385
00:57:18,887 --> 00:57:23,756
- Another lover of yours!
- Yourjealousy has made you mad.

386
00:57:23,927 --> 00:57:27,602
Seize the surgeon
on suspicion of treason.

387
00:57:27,767 --> 00:57:31,965
- Prepare him for torture!
- Confess and we won't hurt you.

388
00:57:32,127 --> 00:57:36,359
- We don't like doing this at all.
- Never!

389
00:57:36,527 --> 00:57:40,122
Bring me the bore worms.

390
00:57:40,287 --> 00:57:44,246
No! Not the bore worms.

391
00:57:47,767 --> 00:57:52,443
l'm a princess. My father
will have your head for this.

392
00:57:52,607 --> 00:57:59,399
He'll execute your whole perverted
secret police. l demand to see him!

393
00:58:00,647 --> 00:58:03,400
With pleasure.

394
00:58:08,767 --> 00:58:12,999
- Father ...
- The traitor is close to confession.

395
00:58:13,167 --> 00:58:17,160
Should we stop the torture?

396
00:58:17,327 --> 00:58:21,115
- No.
- Damn you, father!

397
00:58:27,247 --> 00:58:32,446
- That damn woman's using me again.
- What do you expect?

398
00:58:32,607 --> 00:58:37,886
- l don't know what you see in her.
- Keep playing, fool.

399
00:58:39,887 --> 00:58:46,156
- Fico, l'm going to kill Gordon now.
- And lose the princess forever?

400
00:58:46,327 --> 00:58:52,596
There must be a way to dispose of him
and keep faith with the princess.

401
00:58:52,767 --> 00:58:58,558
- l'm sorry, Flash, l'm finished.
- No, you're not. Get up.

402
00:58:58,727 --> 00:59:02,003
Look, someone's coming.

403
00:59:06,647 --> 00:59:10,242
Send him over. Hurry up.

404
00:59:10,407 --> 00:59:14,719
lt's no good, Flash.
l can't hold on.

405
00:59:14,887 --> 00:59:17,845
Go on, get in.

406
00:59:19,527 --> 00:59:23,406
Sleep well, you traitor.
We hang you in the morning.

407
00:59:30,447 --> 00:59:33,917
- There's always hope.
- This is better.

408
00:59:34,087 --> 00:59:38,444
l stole the key.
We need weapons to cross the swamp.

409
00:59:38,607 --> 00:59:42,043
They're stored in the temple.
Want to climb up with me?

410
00:59:42,207 --> 00:59:45,085
Hold on, Hawkman.

411
00:59:48,487 --> 00:59:52,082
Nice confession. l commend you.

412
00:59:52,247 --> 00:59:57,605
- Execute her.
- No. Too kind.

413
00:59:57,767 --> 01:00:01,362
Aura will be banished to Frigia
after my wedding.

414
01:00:01,527 --> 01:00:06,078
One year in a cavern of ice
will cool her blood.

415
01:00:07,607 --> 01:00:11,646
And then, who knows?

416
01:00:11,807 --> 01:00:17,404
Perhaps we'll marry her to someone
worthy of her treacherous nature.

417
01:00:17,567 --> 01:00:24,962
- How can l express my gratitude?
- Easily. Get me Gordon and Barin.

418
01:00:29,727 --> 01:00:30,682
With pleasure.

419
01:00:53,327 --> 01:00:56,000
Hans, look!

420
01:01:07,247 --> 01:01:11,798
- Hey Vultan!
- Not now.

421
01:01:11,967 --> 01:01:15,721
You'll love this.
See what Brave Blue has caught.

422
01:01:15,887 --> 01:01:19,004
Prince Vultan. Remember us?

423
01:01:20,447 --> 01:01:25,157
lndeed l do, my lovely.

424
01:01:25,327 --> 01:01:29,798
Call the Emperor.
Tell him l have prisoners.

425
01:01:29,967 --> 01:01:33,323
- You wouldn't!
- Are you mad, Vultan?

426
01:01:33,487 --> 01:01:39,278
You hate Ming. You're only waiting
for the moment to attack.

427
01:01:39,447 --> 01:01:42,484
Yes, and Ming knows it, too.

428
01:01:42,647 --> 01:01:47,880
By delivering you,
l allay his suspicions.

429
01:01:48,047 --> 01:01:53,679
- l gain time.
- Our weapons are inferior.

430
01:01:53,847 --> 01:01:58,079
Ming's not unbeatable.
He couldn't even kill Flash.

431
01:01:58,247 --> 01:02:03,560
- Gordon's alive?
- ln Arboria with Prince Barin.

432
01:02:03,727 --> 01:02:05,957
l tell you, now is the time to strike.

433
01:02:18,167 --> 01:02:21,603
- Where are the weapons?
- Feel one.

434
01:02:29,007 --> 01:02:33,956
- Do you know where you are?
- Up the creek.

435
01:02:34,127 --> 01:02:37,437
You've trespassed.

436
01:02:37,607 --> 01:02:43,955
A stranger in this temple
must try the Wood Beast, or die ...

437
01:02:44,127 --> 01:02:46,687
That figures.

438
01:02:49,007 --> 01:02:53,319
You came here of your own free will.
However, -

439
01:02:53,487 --> 01:02:59,084
- because of my word to Aura,
l swear by Arbor l'll not kill you ...

440
01:03:00,247 --> 01:03:03,080
Unless you beg me to.

441
01:03:04,087 --> 01:03:08,046
The Beast lies somewhere
in the stump. Choose a passage.

442
01:03:08,207 --> 01:03:10,437
No way.

443
01:03:15,807 --> 01:03:19,197
- Coward.
- Let's do it.

444
01:03:35,047 --> 01:03:38,517
Must be my lucky day.

445
01:03:38,687 --> 01:03:41,076
You scared?

446
01:03:49,447 --> 01:03:52,678
What would Aura think of you now?

447
01:04:03,687 --> 01:04:06,645
Second down.

448
01:04:12,327 --> 01:04:14,761
Your play.

449
01:04:14,927 --> 01:04:18,124
No, yours.

450
01:04:18,967 --> 01:04:24,644
- Are you sure these are the rules?
- They've just been changed.

451
01:04:47,807 --> 01:04:52,164
Death is certain,
but only after tortured madness.

452
01:04:52,327 --> 01:04:56,525
- How long?
- lt depends on your strength.

453
01:04:57,487 --> 01:05:01,275
Please, end it now.

454
01:05:03,087 --> 01:05:08,115
Tricked you, Barin.
Back off!

455
01:05:08,287 --> 01:05:12,519
One move and you're looking
for a new prince.

456
01:05:15,447 --> 01:05:20,680
Leave him! He's mine.
l hunt him alone.

457
01:06:51,487 --> 01:06:54,126
What the hell is going on?

458
01:07:19,287 --> 01:07:23,644
This is one grave
you won't be returning from.

459
01:07:27,007 --> 01:07:28,281
Vultan wants a word.

460
01:07:47,767 --> 01:07:52,795
Excuse me for waking you. We scanned
a Hawkman patrol 400 Mongo miles east.

461
01:07:52,967 --> 01:07:56,004
They have Gordon and Prince Barin.

462
01:07:58,487 --> 01:08:03,641
- When do we reach Vultan's kingdom?
- Estimating sixteen.

463
01:08:03,807 --> 01:08:07,083
Wake me when it's in sight.

464
01:08:15,647 --> 01:08:20,243
- You'd sell us to Ming?
- Come on, Barin.

465
01:08:20,407 --> 01:08:25,925
Do you expect mercy here? What
would you do if l were your captive?

466
01:08:26,087 --> 01:08:30,683
Remind you of
Article 1<i>7</i> of Ming's Law:

467
01:08:30,847 --> 01:08:34,635
''No prince of Mongo
shall be offered for ransom -

468
01:08:34,807 --> 01:08:38,197
- without trial by combat.''

469
01:08:38,367 --> 01:08:43,361
ls there such an article?
What a damned nuisance.

470
01:08:44,127 --> 01:08:50,441
- And ... who do you choose to fight?
- Him.

471
01:08:54,047 --> 01:08:56,766
This is a lunatic asylum.

472
01:08:57,647 --> 01:09:01,799
- Where are we being taken now?
- Ssh, l'm calculating.

473
01:09:01,967 --> 01:09:07,803
Time remaining before the moon crashes
on Earth. l'd say, roughly ...

474
01:09:08,007 --> 01:09:11,522
Fourteen hours, nine minutes
and <i>tw</i>enty seconds.

475
01:09:11,687 --> 01:09:14,963
And we haven't even found ...
Flash!

476
01:09:20,287 --> 01:09:24,599
Last time l saw you
l prayed it was a dream.

477
01:09:24,767 --> 01:09:29,795
This time l pray it's not.
Are you okay? Me too.

478
01:09:29,967 --> 01:09:35,837
- l've got some crazy stories to tell.
- Save them for our kids.

479
01:09:36,007 --> 01:09:41,639
- Enough!
- Leave us alone! l just got engaged.

480
01:09:54,367 --> 01:09:58,963
Let the combat begin! To the death.

481
01:10:32,127 --> 01:10:34,925
Give me the remote control.

482
01:10:39,127 --> 01:10:41,766
Come on!

483
01:10:46,367 --> 01:10:48,756
He's tilting it.

484
01:10:57,087 --> 01:10:59,282
Watch out!

485
01:11:14,607 --> 01:11:18,361
- Present from Vultan.
- Brute! Give me that.

486
01:11:18,527 --> 01:11:21,519
- Bastard!
- Flash!

487
01:11:27,727 --> 01:11:30,924
Come on, finish him.

488
01:12:03,127 --> 01:12:06,722
Flash! l love you.

489
01:12:06,887 --> 01:12:10,800
But we only have 14 hours
to save the Earth.

490
01:12:26,207 --> 01:12:28,721
How's that feel, Arborian?

491
01:12:39,207 --> 01:12:44,679
lf you kill me, promise to team up
with Vultan and fight Ming.

492
01:12:47,847 --> 01:12:49,963
Goodbye, Barin.

493
01:12:56,967 --> 01:13:01,597
- Take my hand.
- You've won, let him go.

494
01:13:11,847 --> 01:13:14,077
That's it, Prince.

495
01:13:17,327 --> 01:13:20,842
- What is this?
- Humanity.

496
01:13:41,687 --> 01:13:44,963
Where you go, l follow.

497
01:13:48,407 --> 01:13:51,843
Listen to me!

498
01:13:52,647 --> 01:13:56,925
There is something finer
in this galaxy than Ming's law.

499
01:13:57,087 --> 01:13:59,647
Rubbish!

500
01:14:05,527 --> 01:14:08,485
Hawkmen, to your posts!

501
01:14:30,727 --> 01:14:34,322
Agent Zarkov,
you will be liquidated for treachery.

502
01:14:34,487 --> 01:14:38,765
Vultan!
Surrender the fugitives at once, -

503
01:14:38,927 --> 01:14:42,317
- or the lmperial Fleet will blast
your kingdom to atoms.

504
01:14:46,647 --> 01:14:49,525
- Step forward, Barin.
- <i>Prince</i> Barin.

505
01:14:49,687 --> 01:14:55,603
Princess Aura has implicated you
on a charge of high treason.

506
01:14:55,767 --> 01:14:59,362
- A prison ship will take you away.
- You tortured Aura.

507
01:14:59,527 --> 01:15:03,076
lnteresting girl. l think
she found it rather enjoyable.

508
01:15:03,247 --> 01:15:05,715
Klytus.

509
01:15:23,247 --> 01:15:26,762
The first step forward.

510
01:15:26,927 --> 01:15:32,240
lnto the air, Hawkpeople.
Fly for your lives!

511
01:15:32,407 --> 01:15:37,925
You damned hothead, you brought down
destruction on my kingdom.

512
01:15:38,087 --> 01:15:41,318
He showed us the way.
Fight with us.

513
01:15:41,487 --> 01:15:45,844
- Against the lmperial Fleet?
- They won't expect resistance.

514
01:15:46,007 --> 01:15:48,885
- We'll take them by surprise.
- We can do it.

515
01:15:49,047 --> 01:15:56,078
You're all mad! My duty is
to protect my people. Evacuate!

516
01:15:56,247 --> 01:16:00,798
- Then take us with you.
- lmpossible, we can't carry more.

517
01:16:00,967 --> 01:16:04,437
- You're leaving us to die?
- You know Ming's law.

518
01:16:04,607 --> 01:16:08,725
Outside his own kingdom,
the hunter becomes the hunted.

519
01:16:08,887 --> 01:16:14,041
- Traitor!
- Save your breath. Fly!

520
01:16:21,727 --> 01:16:24,002
Help me pull these down.

521
01:16:24,167 --> 01:16:27,159
We'll make parachutes
and jump to Arboria.

522
01:16:27,327 --> 01:16:29,443
We'll kill ourselves.

523
01:16:29,607 --> 01:16:33,885
A body reaches maximum velocity
within a few hundred feet.

524
01:16:34,047 --> 01:16:39,997
- We'll need some rope.
- My God, what is that?

525
01:16:42,087 --> 01:16:47,002
lt's Ming.
We must stop him.

526
01:16:54,287 --> 01:16:57,882
- Blast them?
- Not yet. Send down a shuttle.

527
01:16:58,047 --> 01:17:02,086
- Bring back Barin, Zarkov and Dale.
- And Gordon?

528
01:17:02,247 --> 01:17:06,240
Leave him there.
Prepare my lmperial Lander.

529
01:17:13,367 --> 01:17:16,120
Why aren't l going with them?

530
01:17:17,127 --> 01:17:21,917
- l've got other plans for you.
- l can imagine.

531
01:17:23,287 --> 01:17:29,965
- You want to destroy me.
- lt's the only way to save Earth.

532
01:17:31,047 --> 01:17:35,563
- What if l granted you a kingdom?
- lf you what?

533
01:17:37,247 --> 01:17:41,718
Ming the Merciless,
ruler of the universe, -

534
01:17:41,887 --> 01:17:47,757
- offers Flash Gordon a kingdom
of Mongo, to rule over as his own.

535
01:17:48,807 --> 01:17:54,040
You're crazy. Why would you do that?

536
01:17:54,207 --> 01:17:58,803
Because l've never met your like.
You're a hero, don't you see that?

537
01:17:58,967 --> 01:18:05,679
Who better to rule a kingdom?
Your moon is very close now.

538
01:18:06,727 --> 01:18:12,643
- Earth's end might come within hours.
- You'd call off the attack?

539
01:18:12,807 --> 01:18:15,605
- l could.
- Everyone would be saved?

540
01:18:15,767 --> 01:18:19,237
Yes, and no.

541
01:18:21,407 --> 01:18:26,083
After the earthquakes and tidal waves,
they won't be the same human beings.

542
01:18:26,247 --> 01:18:31,241
They'll be more tractable. Easier
for you to rule, in the name of Ming.

543
01:18:31,407 --> 01:18:38,358
- You mean slaves?
- Let's say 'satisfied with less'.

544
01:18:40,687 --> 01:18:46,637
- What about Dale?
- We have decided to marry her.

545
01:18:47,527 --> 01:18:50,883
She's exceptional.
We'll breed with her -

546
01:18:51,047 --> 01:18:56,246
- and send our progeny back
to populate your Earth.

547
01:18:56,407 --> 01:19:02,801
Do you really prefer death
to a kingdom? l'm disappointed.

548
01:19:02,967 --> 01:19:08,246
l'd rather see you on my side
than scattered into ...

549
01:19:11,327 --> 01:19:13,921
Atoms.

550
01:19:14,087 --> 01:19:17,716
But as you wish.

551
01:19:20,287 --> 01:19:25,884
We'll return to the lmperial Rocket.
Leave the Earthling here to his doom.

552
01:19:39,087 --> 01:19:42,602
- Beam another blast.
- You murderer.

553
01:20:19,367 --> 01:20:22,564
Flash. l loved you.

554
01:20:28,847 --> 01:20:32,726
- They were brave creatures.
- Shut up!

555
01:20:32,887 --> 01:20:39,201
With respect, the man who rid us
of Klytus should not be deserted.

556
01:20:39,367 --> 01:20:45,681
So ... maybe l'd do it different
if l had it over again.

557
01:20:45,847 --> 01:20:52,320
- Then fight.
- l can't help a man who's dead!

558
01:20:52,487 --> 01:20:57,197
Flash Gordon to Vultan.
Mayday, mayday.

559
01:20:59,007 --> 01:21:03,683
This is Vultan. l read you.
Where are you?

560
01:21:03,847 --> 01:21:10,559
- Flying blind on a rocket cycle.
- Flying blind on a rocket cycle?

561
01:21:11,367 --> 01:21:16,122
We're in Arboria.
l'll send you a homing beam.

562
01:21:16,287 --> 01:21:20,599
For what it's worth,
Ming's got Dale, Zarkov and Barin.

563
01:21:22,287 --> 01:21:27,486
- l see. My thanks to you.
- What for?

564
01:21:27,647 --> 01:21:32,721
Well ... for giving a dumb old bird
a second chance.

565
01:21:32,887 --> 01:21:35,879
Over to homing beam.

566
01:21:49,127 --> 01:21:51,641
Don't touch me!

567
01:21:53,847 --> 01:21:57,635
- You!
- Stop! l'm a prisoner too.

568
01:21:57,807 --> 01:22:03,165
Damned Mongo person! You couldn't
tell the truth to save your life.

569
01:22:06,127 --> 01:22:11,679
- Stop! l'm going to be exiled.
- Liar!

570
01:22:11,847 --> 01:22:14,407
Liar.

571
01:22:21,127 --> 01:22:26,599
- ls this another trick, Aura?
- ls this a trick?

572
01:22:28,327 --> 01:22:33,355
Could l cry
if my heart hadn't changed?

573
01:22:33,527 --> 01:22:38,999
l've been such a spoiled fool.
l never knew what my father was ...

574
01:22:39,167 --> 01:22:43,206
Until he let Klytus use bore worms.

575
01:22:43,367 --> 01:22:48,395
l believe you.
But l don't trust you.

576
01:22:48,567 --> 01:22:53,766
You're of Ming's blood. You'll cosy up
with him again in the morning.

577
01:22:53,927 --> 01:22:58,603
Not if you give him this.
lt's deadly poison.

578
01:22:58,767 --> 01:23:02,726
He always drinks a power potion
before making love.

579
01:23:02,887 --> 01:23:09,281
- Drop this into his glass tonight.
- l can't. l gave him my word.

580
01:23:09,447 --> 01:23:13,440
- What word?
- To be a good wife ...

581
01:23:13,607 --> 01:23:17,202
lf he'd spare Zarkov and Barin.
He vowed he would.

582
01:23:17,367 --> 01:23:22,236
My father has never kept a vow.

583
01:23:22,407 --> 01:23:26,764
Keeping our word is one of the things
that make us better than you.

584
01:23:28,807 --> 01:23:34,882
A guard will take you to the waiting
room. Your Joyous Time has come.

585
01:23:35,047 --> 01:23:38,642
You are to be prepared
for your wedding.

586
01:23:39,607 --> 01:23:43,520
l'm lost. Nothing can save me now.

587
01:23:58,487 --> 01:24:01,604
Flash Gordon approaching.

588
01:24:01,767 --> 01:24:06,318
What do you mean,
'Flash Gordon approaching'?

589
01:24:06,487 --> 01:24:11,003
<i>on a rocket cycle.</i>
<i>Shall l inform His Majesty?</i>

590
01:24:11,167 --> 01:24:15,638
The Emperor would shoot you
for interrupting his wedding.

591
01:24:15,807 --> 01:24:18,401
Fire when Gordon's in range.

592
01:24:38,727 --> 01:24:44,359
He's escaping, idiot!
Dispatch War Rocket Ajax.

593
01:25:04,687 --> 01:25:07,076
Charge the boosters.

594
01:25:16,767 --> 01:25:21,966
- Flash Gordon in range, Captain.
- Fire!

595
01:25:27,527 --> 01:25:31,918
- Shall we go in after him?
- No. Reduce velocity.

596
01:25:38,807 --> 01:25:43,961
Our trap worked.
They'll follow me for sure.

597
01:25:44,127 --> 01:25:46,800
Stand by, my Hawkmen!

598
01:25:51,127 --> 01:25:55,757
- He's not coming out, sir.
- Prepare to electrify cloud.

599
01:25:56,927 --> 01:26:02,399
Prepare sky nets to catch
Gordon's body. Fire capacitators.

600
01:26:08,167 --> 01:26:12,843
- They're trying to flush you out.
- Let's go in.

601
01:26:19,767 --> 01:26:23,806
Good. They're coming through.

602
01:26:47,087 --> 01:26:51,365
Squadron 40 ... Dive!

603
01:27:07,927 --> 01:27:10,316
Arm topside!

604
01:27:24,007 --> 01:27:26,999
Second wave. Dive!

605
01:27:57,607 --> 01:28:00,167
Stop engines. Repel boarders.

606
01:28:40,207 --> 01:28:45,406
- Biro's hit. l'm going in after him.
- lmpetuous boy.

607
01:28:47,847 --> 01:28:51,965
Oh well, who wants to live forever?

608
01:28:54,087 --> 01:28:56,555
Dive!

609
01:29:50,007 --> 01:29:52,646
Biro, hold on, l'm coming.

610
01:29:54,527 --> 01:29:59,157
- You all right?
- They winged me. Detonate the mine.

611
01:30:03,847 --> 01:30:06,122
Blow it, Flash!

612
01:30:12,047 --> 01:30:15,039
Let's get out of here.

613
01:30:20,967 --> 01:30:24,676
Well done, Flash. Here.
Up there, Luro!

614
01:30:24,847 --> 01:30:27,236
Come on.

615
01:30:32,447 --> 01:30:35,200
Full velocity, all drives.

616
01:30:54,767 --> 01:30:57,645
<i>Attention, all citizens.</i>

617
01:30:57,807 --> 01:31:02,005
<i>Behold the face</i>
<i>of your Empress to be.</i>

618
01:31:04,527 --> 01:31:10,124
While you await the ceremony,
all channels will display -

619
01:31:10,287 --> 01:31:14,405
- the execution of the traitors,
Barin and Zarkov.

620
01:31:27,167 --> 01:31:30,000
Pick that up, would you?

621
01:31:38,367 --> 01:31:40,961
Tell me more about this Houdini.

622
01:31:42,327 --> 01:31:45,399
This is it.
At least it'll be over quickly.

623
01:31:52,847 --> 01:31:57,284
Scanner malfunction,
area <i>7-7</i> delta, under repair.

624
01:32:08,247 --> 01:32:12,081
- They've changed the code.
- l've changed too, Aura.

625
01:32:12,247 --> 01:32:16,035
- l think l can work it out.
- Will you marry me?

626
01:32:16,207 --> 01:32:20,644
We'll try.
Not now, Barin!

627
01:32:20,807 --> 01:32:23,526
lf l'm not at the wedding,
l'll be shot.

628
01:32:23,687 --> 01:32:28,602
l thought it was the Zeitman series!
l haven't changed.

629
01:32:35,167 --> 01:32:40,480
Everybody take off! Form a battle
stream behind the rocket.

630
01:32:40,647 --> 01:32:44,162
Flash and me bail out
when the shooting starts.

631
01:32:44,327 --> 01:32:49,481
- And keep your head down.
- See you in Mingo City.

632
01:32:49,647 --> 01:32:55,358
Yes ... with luck.
What are you setting there?

633
01:32:55,527 --> 01:33:00,362
That's the time left for the Earth.
ln minutes and seconds.

634
01:33:01,687 --> 01:33:06,363
- Level with me. Will this do it?
- Yes, no doubt.

635
01:33:06,527 --> 01:33:10,884
There's a lightning field at the
entrance. When this baby hits it ...

636
01:33:12,327 --> 01:33:18,436
lt will blow that field dead.
My Hawkmen fly right in.

637
01:33:18,607 --> 01:33:21,883
Let's see what Mingo City's saying.

638
01:33:28,407 --> 01:33:29,999
Oh, my God.

639
01:34:00,527 --> 01:34:03,837
- Rocket Ajax returning.
- With Gordon's body?

640
01:34:04,007 --> 01:34:06,999
l presume so. Communications are off.

641
01:34:07,167 --> 01:34:12,958
- Are they in the proper approach?
- <i>Negative.</i>

642
01:34:13,127 --> 01:34:17,120
- Open fire!
<i>- on Ajax?</i>

643
01:34:17,287 --> 01:34:22,122
<i>All weapons, now!</i>
<i>Charge the lightning field.</i>

644
01:34:22,287 --> 01:34:26,838
l take responsibility,
in the Emperor's name.

645
01:34:33,847 --> 01:34:38,284
Attention, all wedding guests.
There is no cause for alarm.

646
01:34:38,447 --> 01:34:42,679
The weapons are being fired
in continuous salute, -

647
01:34:42,847 --> 01:34:46,556
- in honor of His Majesty's wedding.

648
01:34:52,767 --> 01:34:56,840
Come on, Flash.
lt's time to bail out.

649
01:34:57,007 --> 01:35:01,478
Sorry, l'm not coming.
The rocket cycle's gone.

650
01:35:01,647 --> 01:35:05,879
- l'll carry you.
- Bail out, Vultan.

651
01:35:06,047 --> 01:35:09,642
- Are you crazy?
- The fire's too heavy.

652
01:35:09,807 --> 01:35:13,083
We'll never make it
with nobody at the wheel.

653
01:35:13,247 --> 01:35:17,684
- lt's suicide, Flash!
- No. A rational transaction.

654
01:35:17,847 --> 01:35:21,965
- One life for billions.
- You'll be destroyed!

655
01:35:22,127 --> 01:35:25,597
Looney bird!
Get out of here, they need you.

656
01:35:25,767 --> 01:35:31,876
- Goodbye, Flash, it's been ...
- l know. For me too, Vultan.

657
01:35:32,927 --> 01:35:36,397
Tell Dale l know
it would've been good.

658
01:35:36,567 --> 01:35:40,116
You must come from
one hell of a planet.

659
01:35:40,287 --> 01:35:43,359
Not too bad.

660
01:35:53,127 --> 01:35:56,915
Onward, my brave Hawkmen.

661
01:35:57,087 --> 01:36:02,639
Let this be known forever
as Flash Gordon's Day!

662
01:36:05,407 --> 01:36:11,039
- Freeze, you bloody bastards!
- Take us to Ming.

663
01:36:11,207 --> 01:36:14,961
We do not lead traitors
to the Emperor.

664
01:36:15,127 --> 01:36:20,247
We'll find a way.
Grab an imager off an agent.

665
01:36:27,087 --> 01:36:29,601
Zarkov!

666
01:36:33,407 --> 01:36:36,683
- Thank you.
<i>- Ajax still approaching.</i>

667
01:36:36,847 --> 01:36:39,486
<i>ldentified Earthling Gordon</i>
<i>at the controls.</i>

668
01:36:39,647 --> 01:36:44,721
<i>We guarantee its destruction in</i>
<i>the lightning field. General Kala?</i>

669
01:36:44,887 --> 01:36:48,516
<i>Please show yourself.</i>

670
01:36:48,687 --> 01:36:53,124
- Let's go.
- We must deactivate the field.

671
01:36:53,287 --> 01:36:57,644
- Where are the atomic generators?
- There's no time.

672
01:36:57,807 --> 01:37:02,403
l'm heading for Sector Alpha 9.
Hold the fort.

673
01:37:17,047 --> 01:37:21,040
There must be a way of
deactivating the lightning field.

674
01:37:52,887 --> 01:37:56,880
Do you, Ming the Merciless,
ruler of the universe, -

675
01:37:57,047 --> 01:38:01,359
- take this Earthling, Dale Arden,
to be your Empress of the hour?

676
01:38:01,527 --> 01:38:07,443
- Of the hour, yes.
- Do you promise to use her?

677
01:38:07,607 --> 01:38:14,365
Not to blast her into space ...
until you grow weary of her?

678
01:38:14,527 --> 01:38:17,280
- l do.
- l do not!

679
01:38:41,887 --> 01:38:46,642
Recite after me, Your Majesty.
With this ring ...

680
01:38:46,807 --> 01:38:50,686
Matsuna! Ring! Ring!

681
01:38:55,047 --> 01:39:00,326
Recite after me, Your Majesty.
With this ring l thee wed.

682
01:39:02,127 --> 01:39:04,960
Dale, what a damn shame.

683
01:39:10,727 --> 01:39:14,845
Freeze!
Deactivate the lightning field.

684
01:39:37,727 --> 01:39:40,321
- Gordon!
- Flash?

685
01:40:23,767 --> 01:40:29,478
The game's lost. Stop your attack
on Earth, and l'll spare your life.

686
01:40:30,887 --> 01:40:34,197
You pitiful fool.

687
01:40:34,367 --> 01:40:39,157
My life is not
for any Earthling to give, -

688
01:40:39,327 --> 01:40:41,841
- or take.

689
01:40:45,447 --> 01:40:48,359
Your power's fading, Ming.

690
01:41:11,727 --> 01:41:14,958
The reactors are destroyed.
Glad you made it, Vultan.

691
01:41:15,127 --> 01:41:17,960
Better late than never.

692
01:41:18,127 --> 01:41:21,403
- Dale.
- Look out, Flash.

693
01:41:21,567 --> 01:41:25,526
Don't move. Stay where you are.

694
01:41:26,767 --> 01:41:32,319
<i>Long live Flash. You've saved</i>
<i>your Earth. Have a nice day.</i>

695
01:41:41,527 --> 01:41:45,520
Barin is the rightful heir.

696
01:41:45,687 --> 01:41:49,441
Hail Barin, King of Mongo.

697
01:41:49,607 --> 01:41:53,520
We owe everything to Flash.

698
01:41:53,687 --> 01:41:58,158
We appoint Vultan
General of our armies.

699
01:42:00,847 --> 01:42:06,399
From this day on, let every breed
of Mongo live together in peace.

700
01:42:08,727 --> 01:42:13,562
- Will we ever get out of here, Hans?
- l don't know.

701
01:42:13,727 --> 01:42:17,959
- But we'll try.
- We certainly invite you all to stay.

702
01:42:18,127 --> 01:42:22,518
- What do you think?
- l'm a New York City girl.

703
01:42:24,247 --> 01:42:28,240
lt's a little too quiet around here
for me.

